pageTitle: County clerk’s office to close for Good Friday | TheAndersonNews.com
TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {20430=The Anderson County Clerk’s office will be closed Friday, March 29 in recognition of Good Friday. Denny said the office will reopen April 1, and suggested those who need to pay vehicle taxes and renew registrations do so by March 28 to avoid having those items expire. The clerk’s office is normally open Mondays from 8:30 a.m. to 6 p.m., and Tuesday through Friday from 8:30 a.m. to 5 p.m., 26078=The Anderson News | circulation@theandersonnews.com | 502-839-6906 P.O. Box 410, 504 W. Broadway, Suite D, Lawrenceburg, KY 40342 Office Hours are 8:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m., Monday through Friday, 34215=Copyright © 2015}
